label.value: nipple development

value.value: The progression of the nipple over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The nipple is a part of the mammary gland that protrudes from the surface ectoderm.

label.value: cell migration involved in mammary placode formation

value.value: The orderly movement of epithelial cells within the mammary line that contributes to the formation of the mammary placode.

label.value: regulation of cholesterol import

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cholesterol import. Cholesterol import is the directed movement of cholesterol into a cell or organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of cholesterol import

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of cholesterol import. Cholesterol import is the directed movement of cholesterol into a cell or organelle.

label.value: regulation of ascospore wall beta-glucan biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of ascospore wall beta-glucan biosynthetic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of beta-glucans, compounds composed of glucose residues linked by beta-D-glucosidic bonds, found in the walls of ascospores.

label.value: regulation of chromosome condensation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of chromosome condensation, the progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis, in eukaryotic cells.

label.value: regulation of ascospore wall (1->3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of ascospore wall (1->3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucans, compounds composed of glucose residues linked by (1->3)-beta-D--glucosidic bonds, found in the walls of ascospores.

label.value: regulation of protein deneddylation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of protein deneddylation, the removal of a ubiquitin-like protein of the NEDD8 type from a protein.

label.value: regulation of vesicle-mediated transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of vesicle-mediated transport, the directed movement of substances, either within a vesicle or in the vesicle membrane, into, out of or within a cell.

label.value: regulation of ER to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of ER to Golgi vesicle-mediated transport, the directed movement of substances from the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) to the Golgi, mediated by COP II vesicles. Small COP II coated vesicles form from the ER and then fuse directly with the cis-Golgi. Larger structures are transported along microtubules to the cis-Golgi.

label.value: regulation of homologous chromosome segregation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of homologous chromosome segregation, the cell cycle process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the first division of the meiotic cell cycle. Each replicated chromosome, composed of two sister chromatids, aligns at the cell equator, paired with its homologous partner; this pairing off, referred to as synapsis, permits genetic recombination. One homolog (both sister chromatids) of each morphologic type goes into each of the resulting chromosome sets.

label.value: regulation of meiosis I

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of meiosis I, a cell cycle process comprising the steps by which a cell progresses through the first phase of meiosis, in which cells divide and homologous chromosomes are paired and segregated from each other, producing two daughter cells.

label.value: regulation of microtubule-based movement

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of microtubule-based movement, the movement of organelles, other microtubules and other particles along microtubules, mediated by motor proteins.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription initiation by RNA polymerase II

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of a process involved in starting transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: regulation of 4,6-pyruvylated galactose residue biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of 4,6-pyruvylated galactose residue biosynthetic process, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of the pyruvylated galactose residue 4-6-O-[(R)(1-carboxyethylidine)]-Gal-beta-(1->3)-. The galactose residue is part of a larger polysaccharide chain.

label.value: positive regulation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucans.

label.value: negative regulation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucan biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of (1->3)-beta-D-glucans.

label.value: positive regulation of lactation by mesenchymal-epithelial cell signaling

value.value: The process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of lactation as a result of the secretion of a signal from the mammary fat and its reception by a mammary epithelial cell.

label.value: mesenchymal-epithelial cell signaling

value.value: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a mesenchymal cell to an epithelial cell where it is received and interpreted.

label.value: positive regulation of salivary gland formation by mesenchymal-epithelial signaling

value.value: Any process that induces the formation of the salivary gland field by means of the secretion of a signal by a mesenchymal cell and its reception and interpretation by an epithelial cell resulting in it adopting the identity of a salivary gland bud cell.

label.value: positive regulation of dentin-containing tooth bud formation by mesenchymal-epithelial signaling

value.value: Any process that initiates the formation of a tooth bud by the secretion of a signal from a mesenchymal cell and its reception and subsequent change in the identity of an epithelial cell of the tooth bud.

label.value: mammary gland duct regression in males

value.value: The process in which the epithelium of the mammary duct is destroyed in males.

label.value: white fat cell differentiation involved in mammary gland fat development

value.value: The process in which a preadipocyte acquires specialized features of a white adipocyte of the mammary gland. White adipocytes have cytoplasmic lipids arranged in a unique vacuole.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in mammary gland bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a cell of the mammary placode becomes a cell of the mammary gland bud.

label.value: mammary gland epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell becomes a more specialized epithelial cell of the mammary gland.

label.value: peripheral mammary gland bud epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell of the mammary placode becomes an epithelial cell at the periphery of the mammary gland bud. Cells at the periphery of the bud are larger that those of the surrounding epithelium and are arranged concentrically.

label.value: internal mammary gland bud epithelial cell differentiation

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell of the mammary placode becomes an internal epithelial cell of the mammary gland bud. Internal cells are small and of irregular shape.

label.value: mesenchymal cell condensation involved in mammary fat development

value.value: The cell adhesion process in which mammary mesenchyme cells adhere to one another in the initial stages of the formation of mammary fat development.

label.value: mammary gland bud morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which anatomical structures of the mammary gland buds are generated and organized. Mammary gland buds form by an outpocketing of the mammary placodes and grow to invade the mammary fat, when they form the mammary cord.

label.value: mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: The process in which the mammary gland bud grows along its axis.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of mammary gland bud epithelial cells, resulting in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in mammary gland bud elongation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mammary gland bud epithelial cell proliferation that results in the elongation of the bud.

label.value: mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which anatomical structures of the mammary gland cord are generated and organized. Mammary gland cords form when the mammary gland bud invades the mammary fat.

label.value: epithelial cell differentiation involved in mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which a relatively unspecialized epithelial cell becomes a more specialized epithelial cell of the mammary gland cord. Epithelial cells of the mammary cord give it its funnel-like shape and some are cornified.

label.value: mammary gland cord elongation

value.value: The process in which the mammary gland sprout grows along its axis.

label.value: branching involved in mammary gland cord morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the branching structure of the mammary gland cord is generated and organized. The mammary gland cord is a solid epithelial structure that will hollow out, forming the mammary duct.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in mammary cord morphogenesis by fat precursor cell-epithelial cell signaling

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching of the mammary gland cord as a result of a signal being created by a mammary fat precursor cell and its subsequent reception and interpretation by a mammary cord epithelial cell.

label.value: regulation of mammary gland cord elongation by mammary fat precursor cell-epithelial cell signaling

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of mammary gland cord elongation as a result of a signal being created by a mesenchymal cell that is a precursor to the mammary fat and its subsequent reception and interpretation by an mammary cord epithelial cell.

label.value: nipple morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the nipple is generated and organized.

label.value: nipple sheath formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the nipple sheath from the unspecified epidermis. This process begins with a circular ingrowth of the epidermis around the region of the mammary sprout. It ends before the region begins to elevate.

label.value: epidermis morphogenesis involved in nipple formation

value.value: The process in which the epidermis of the nipple sheath is uplifted to form an umbrella-like projection.

label.value: submandibular salivary gland formation

value.value: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a submandibular salivary gland. This process begins with a thickening of the epithelium next to the tongue and ends when a bud linked to the oral surface is formed.

label.value: salivary gland cavitation

value.value: The process in which the solid core of salivary epithelium gives rise to the hollow tube of the gland.

label.value: apoptotic process involved in salivary gland cavitation

value.value: Any apoptotic process in which the solid core of the gland is hollowed out to form the duct.

label.value: epithelial cell proliferation involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells of the submandibular salivary gland, resulting in the expansion of a cell population and the shaping of the gland.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis by mesenchymal-epithelial signaling

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis as a result of signals being generated by the mesenchyme and received and interpreted by the salivary gland epithelium.

label.value: dichotomous subdivision of terminal units involved in salivary gland branching

value.value: The process in which a salivary epithelial cord bifurcates at its end.

label.value: branch elongation involved in salivary gland morphogenesis

value.value: The differential growth of the salivary branches along their axis, resulting in the growth of a branch.

label.value: regulation of branching involved in salivary gland morphogenesis by extracellular matrix-epithelial cell signaling

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of salivary gland branching as a result of the transfer of information from the extracellular matrix to the epithelium of the salivary gland.

label.value: embryonic placenta morphogenesis

value.value: The process in which the embryonic placenta is generated and organized.
